<Author>NorthamptonHammer
<Content>Hotel Mondial superb value! Returned from Hotel Mondial  having read all the reviews of this hotel, will state that is superb.Rooms are a more than generous size , spotlessly clean  in our case overlooking the Kurfurstendamm, where the christmas lights twinkled.The hotel is close to s-bahn station  bus stops for tours.breakfasts (included in the price) are staggering..ample portions to help your self  top quality fruits , cereals , cooked dishes etc.On one occasion the hotel was booked for dinner for a group booking so we went just around the corner where there are IIndian, Spanish  French restaurants.Quite close is the zoo-ological gardens where the christmas markets are (one of I think about 8 altogether)  it is enchanting.To get the best of Berlin, take a bus tour to hop on  off..so much tto see.One trip you can do on your own is the Sachsenhausen concentration camp, just outside the city...harrowing but interesting.Berlin is trying to come to terms with the horror of the nazis  seems to be forever apologising showing so many aspects of the war all over town.One tip, if you stay here get off the s-bahn at Savigny platz on s9 it is quite close.This train runs from the airport which is about 20 miles away  costs just over $2.We paid around 拢75 a night for this hotel,  considered it excellent value for money. Staff Friendly  helpful. The desk clerk even wished us a safe journey home. Highly recommended. 
